Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.00,0:01:42.37,Top,,0,0,0,,We’ve stirred up quite a few commotions \Nsince we came to St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.37,0:01:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And it finally caught up with us the other day. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.07,0:01:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After we turned in our French homework \Nin the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.08,0:01:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we were summoned by the Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.51,0:01:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And our classmates seem to get annoyed \Nby just about everything we do.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.82,0:01:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like this kind of thing \Nwill just keep happening! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.20,0:02:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, you made the same mistake \Non that same question again.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.94,0:02:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you prepare for the lesson?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.79,0:02:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I did! Though, I've been busy with this and that... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.11,0:02:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your attitude isn’t at all \Nlike the one of someone who’s really trying.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.02,0:02:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes... {doesn't really work but idk how the previous line could possibly be turned into a question}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.51,0:02:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Work through these questions \Nand hand them in again before the final bell today. {lit: before after-school}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.50,0:02:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.99,0:02:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have a deal, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.84,0:02:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.47,0:02:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what a pity.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.33,0:02:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't Pat going to go and see \Nthe concert after school today?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.60,0:02:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.66,0:02:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.30,0:02:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.43,0:02:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to the concert is all very well,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.94,0:02:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s no excuse to neglect your duties \Nor your own improvement.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.34,0:02:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the sort of young ladies \Nyou ought to strive to be.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.48,0:03:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, turn to page 45.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.09,0:03:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts is unusually strict \Nfor someone with her face.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.13,0:03:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.49,0:03:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did God create maths in this world at all?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.14,0:03:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I fail to see how working through all those equations with ease will help me in life.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.94,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.22,0:03:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Studying maths helps you \Norganize your thoughts.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.17,0:03:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts said it can even enrich your ideas.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.21,0:03:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? \NI was looking forward to that concert...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.28,0:03:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, how about secretly finishing it \Nduring history class? {lit: hey, if you naishoku'd it during the next history class?; naishoku = (secretly) working on something unrelated to the class (or conference, etc.) one is attending}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.70,0:03:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Secretly finish it? {naishoku}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.65,0:03:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.75,0:03:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore the history class \Nand do your math homework instead.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.56,0:03:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you really do that? {lit: is that kind of thing heiki? - heiki = all right/no problem}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.09,0:03:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can! {heiki}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.22,0:03:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it’s taught by Miss Kennedy.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.93,0:03:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.26,0:03:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she’ll be coming to take \NMiss Lewis’s place, as she’s taken ill.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.93,0:03:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And Janet says that Miss Kennedy \Ndoesn't belong in this profession. {lit: made a mistake by becoming a teacher}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.40,0:03:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.40,0:03:56.69,Overlap,,0,0,0,,What, why?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.02,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.88,0:04:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please keep quiet!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.56,0:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I see now.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.08,0:04:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then I might as well \Ntry sneaking in some maths... {naishoku}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.79,0:04:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.86,0:04:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Hilary does it too.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.48,0:04:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,See? Now, where was I...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.98,0:04:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, really? \NThat sounds made up!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.70,0:04:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it down, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.95,0:04:29.64,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Wait, really? {???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.64,0:04:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet! Go back to your seat!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.37,0:04:32.92,Overlap,,0,0,0,,So what happened next? {???????? not a clue, making up from previous sentences}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.31,0:04:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.46,0:04:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry, I didn't mean to...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.41,0:04:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... The notes I made \Nfor the solved maths problems...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.25,0:04:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Maths?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.17,0:04:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I... {??? likely "matte" = wait}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.41,0:04:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Maths...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.58,0:04:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Maths, right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.43,0:05:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.01,0:05:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, let's head out!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.25,0:05:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! {could be "yeah, kay" I don't remember what she looked like}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.15,0:05:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, what a pity! \NDoing Miss Roberts’ homework?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.62,0:05:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.75,0:05:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the good work.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.06,0:05:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Going out somewhere?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.34,0:05:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we’re off to see a concert.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.26,0:05:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good for you. With a fluttering ribbon and all—\Nprobably the height of fashion for a St. Clare’s girl. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.27,0:05:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.54,0:05:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Look who's talking—a girl who has to stay behind and study extra hours! {ochikobore}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.50,0:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No one ever dared speak about us \Nlike that at our old school.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.44,0:05:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the program... {/studying}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.53,0:05:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to teach us differently at our old school, \Nwhich is why we're so confused here.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.05,0:05:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.22,0:05:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it that all we ever hear is, \N“our old school, our old school, our old school…”?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.36,0:06:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“The O’Sullivans used to be the best\N at studying, sports, and everything else!” {not sure what to make of that tsu tsu, probably means the sound of seething pat and isa supposedly make when they talk about how great they were at their old school?}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.46,0:06:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“We're not going to clean the seniors' boots!”
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.51,0:06:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.33,0:06:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You call that humour? Pathetic! {????; also using british spelling}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.51,0:06:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unseemly indeed. {/cruel}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.58,0:06:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you embarrassed of yourselves?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.27,0:06:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.02,0:06:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who does she think she is?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.66,0:06:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.91,0:06:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you mean by that?! {probably the "embarrased" line}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.73,0:06:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t forget, we pride ourselves \Non our witty and refined humour.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.74,0:06:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we find yours to be a crude embarrassment!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.84,0:06:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen here, you... {itta wa ne? then it would be "Now you've said it..." but that doesn't flow into the next line}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.14,0:06:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I pride myself on never doing anything cowardly \Nand on having the best sense of humour in the class!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.73,0:06:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you’d best stop taking pride \Nin that, starting today. {lit: throw that pride away}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.58,0:06:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you even know about real humour?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.68,0:06:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.75,0:06:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not done here!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.02,0:07:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve yet to show you \Njust how good my sense of humour is!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.82,0:07:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the subject would be... {/topic/theme/subject}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.16,0:07:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy’s class is first thing tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.66,0:07:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a carefree morning. {lit: from the morning, we'll be able to take a breather - in the sense "take it easy"}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.16,0:07:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We'll make it Miss Kennedy. {the subject}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.56,0:07:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it, twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.43,0:07:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, I’ll turn history class \Ninto a whirlwind of laughter!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.38,0:07:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do to make them \Npay attention in class?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.29,0:07:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She's here. {?? kita wa yo?}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.53,0:07:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's the day I do it right. {/I do my best}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.62,0:07:56.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,They're all in their seats!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.31,0:08:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see someone even prepared the map? \NThank you very much!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.62,0:08:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I want to tell you how the people of England \Nlived in the seventeenth century.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.99,0:08:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, in the seventeenth century...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.61,0:08:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It won't write! \NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.07,0:08:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.55,0:08:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, what kind of prank is that? {???? mattaku nante itazura suru no?}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.10,0:08:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, how strange. \NWhat's with this chalk?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.46,0:08:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that awful sound?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.34,0:08:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the squeaky chalk. {lit: chalk that makes sounds}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.78,0:08:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you manage \Nto swap it with the teacher’s?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.95,0:08:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is impossible for the great Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.42,0:08:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So childish. {lit: childish mischief - dunno how to make it sound derisive}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.22,0:08:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just getting started.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.82,0:08:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What am I going to do with this?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.97,0:08:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy, behind you! {lit: look behind}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.40,0:08:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.48,0:09:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's going a bit too far. \NAny prank should have a limit, you know! {??????? no clue what's that kareto}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.45,0:09:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, would you look at Pat! \NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.63,0:09:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so good about this? \NJust some corny tricks. {/lame/tasteless}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.56,0:09:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.90,0:09:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how about you demonstrate to us \Nyour sense of humour?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.27,0:09:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.47,0:09:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Miss Kennedy, I have a question.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.42,0:09:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.91,0:09:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, Patricia. What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.39,0:09:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Did people wear clothes \Nin the seventeenth century, or just skins? {from book}{kawa = skin; hide; pelt}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.36,0:09:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, They weren't cavemen! \NSurely you know that they wore clothes! {lit: it wasn't a primitive era}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.80,0:09:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? So then, did people in the seventeenth century have no skin? {hifu = skin (specifically as organ) - don't think there's a way to differentiate it in english, and the original book didn't have that}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.26,0:09:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even their own skin? {from book; lit: hifu should be kawa too}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.99,0:09:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's true, b-but you see... {she's agreeing so idk, maybe she's meaning to correct her that hifu is not kawa ???}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.20,0:10:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How lackluster. {imaichi = not quite (right); not very good; somewhat (lacking)}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.33,0:10:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Total flop. {??????????????? not in the book, nijuugoten would usually mean "25 points" but I have no clue what it could possibly mean; she's kinda seen smiling here so maybe she half-approves it, as in "50/50"; could also be something "that one doesn't make sense/doesn't land"?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.70,0:10:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That joke wasn't any good at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.90,0:10:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.42,0:10:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Somebody please take this poster away. {/clean up}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.08,0:10:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.88,0:10:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go, the finishing touch! {finishing blow; coup de grâce​}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.65,0:10:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,J-Janet?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.12,0:10:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.73,0:10:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.52,0:10:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Two...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.26,0:10:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.46,0:10:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.78,0:10:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, stop...!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.14,0:10:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.31,0:10:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected from Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.45,0:10:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a legend, Janet. {/the best}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.92,0:10:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a genius at humour!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.38,0:10:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you even come up with a prank like that? {in the book at least they did it simultaneously to startle kennedy and it made some sense, though it was still lame, here they changed that to some silly "another brick in the wall" shit so even this line sound off, like what was there to come up with, genius}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.79,0:10:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My brain's just built different,\N unlike someone else here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.06,0:10:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That know-it-all... {shhhh}{/So frustrating...} {Was "bitch", leaving it as a comment so we can see if jme reads the comments.}{:TRUE:}{Fuckin' kill yourselves, holy fuckin' shit}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.46,0:11:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh... No more! {????????? no clue what she says, maybe "come on, there should be one" or "oh, found one!"}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.76,0:11:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.16,0:11:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A toy store!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.70,0:11:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I need some new toys \Nto keep up with Janet. {not exactly some conventional toys but rather "tools for pranks" but idk if there's a fitting english word for that}{also not sure what that dashi ni iku means, maybe "put one over on janet"???}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.80,0:11:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you think I'd just suck it up \Nand accept defeat? {lit: did you think I'll lose by continuing things to be as is}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.50,0:11:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea you and Janet were so alike.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.42,0:11:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.88,0:11:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See? When you get stubborn \Nand fly off the handle, you lose all sense. {lit: when stubborn and flare up, you're both indiscriminate - think that last one means they lack a strong moral compass, or more specifically, would target a defenseless and weak teacher}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.25,0:11:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite all that, you’re really quite simple \Nand good-natured at heart. {????????? no clue what's that ne wa tanjun; also not sure if these traits are shared with janet or specific to pat}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.25,0:11:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true! \NDon't lump me in with the likes of Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.08,0:11:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.94,0:12:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then! \NI'll find them on my own!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.15,0:12:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.09,0:12:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.11,0:12:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Gee, Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.08,0:12:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{Papa, this one is fun!}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.30,0:12:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't do.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.57,0:12:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they have \Nsomething more unusual here.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.87,0:12:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that'd leave Janet speechless. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.98,0:12:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just too dull.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.05,0:12:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they have \Nsomething more unusual here.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.55,0:12:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that'd leave Pat speechless... {same line as before}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.45,0:12:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.65,0:12:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.85,0:12:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{humph}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.67,0:12:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't lose next time! {/next time}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.42,0:12:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? Too bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.02,0:12:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm gonna win the next one too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.06,0:12:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I already have a special trick \Nready up my sleeve.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.86,0:12:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Special trick?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.85,0:12:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.33,0:12:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect a parcel from my brother to come today.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.85,0:12:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A parcel full of firecrackers! {again, using the spelling from book, idk maybe firecrackers wasn't british spelling or wasn't prevalent yet - Nah, screw that. Anime subs are not a novel}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.60,0:12:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Firecrackers?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.10,0:12:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I'll plant them under the teacher's desk, \Nand they'll go "Pow-pow" all at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.81,0:12:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine Miss Kennedy's face when that happens!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.44,0:13:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd surely scare the pants off Miss Kennedy! {lit: make her jump from surprise}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.68,0:13:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it were me, \NI'd plant them in the stove.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.02,0:13:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The stove?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.92,0:13:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratatata!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.85,0:13:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Explosion!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.04,0:13:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my idea, though!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.22,0:13:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have figured it out even without your help! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.49,0:13:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not do it, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.33,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I jolly will!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.06,0:13:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.22,0:13:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could that be?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.49,0:13:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{arararara}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.26,0:13:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.50,0:13:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me help you.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.73,0:13:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.74,0:14:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your help, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.21,0:14:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this your room?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.35,0:14:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.83,0:14:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the books in here are about history?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.94,0:14:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, each thing I look into leads to another, \Nand before I know it, my room’s crammed with books.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.36,0:14:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I take a peek into some of them?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.46,0:14:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, by all means.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.83,0:14:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the first student \Nto ever come to my room.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.56,0:14:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I would love it. {lit: big welcome [to you taking interest in my books]}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.76,0:14:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an illustrated guide \Nto Ancient Greece—isn't it wonderful?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.07,0:14:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So pretty...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.27,0:14:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Parthenon, the ruins of Troy, \Nand the legends of various gods.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.17,0:14:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m studying history, \NI fully lose track of time.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.11,0:14:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A heroic epic, a beautiful work of art. {lit: a drama about heroes}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.76,0:14:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an emotional person, so I want to share \Nthis excitement with everyone else.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.09,0:14:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,With us?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.90,0:14:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Just look—I make notes every night \Nfor the next day’s class. {probably means "lesson plan"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.06,0:14:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can never follow through with them, \Nbecause I lose control of the class. {lit: But I'm clumsy and I can't transmit/communicate it well - meaning "I can't keep my class in check and it always turns into a circus, so I can't finish the lesson as planned"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.36,0:15:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel so guilty towards my students \Nand Miss Lewis, whom I’m standing in for.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.82,0:15:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I were a better teacher... \NNow, where was it...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.87,0:15:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.26,0:15:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! If I can explain this one piece properly, \NI’m sure it will spark everyone’s interest. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.78,0:15:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.15,0:15:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Are those firecrackers? {using the spelling from earlier}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.26,0:15:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like fun!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.62,0:15:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's use them soon, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.12,0:15:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you watch.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.19,0:15:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna do?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.59,0:15:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll plant them in the stove.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.30,0:15:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great idea.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.70,0:15:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.82,0:15:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Get seated, everybody. \NMiss Kennedy is here.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.97,0:15:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.91,0:15:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.98,0:15:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.06,0:16:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right... There's something \NI'd like to say to you today.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.06,0:16:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe I've been a bit too lenient up until now. {negative; passive; half-hearted; unmotivated​ - meaning "inactive in enforcing discipline"}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.68,0:16:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, your history classes... {???? lit: everyone's history... - dunno what's implied next}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.66,0:16:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What on Earth is going on in there?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.74,0:16:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm scared, Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.63,0:16:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.73,0:16:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.45,0:16:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, Janet, it’s probably a very gassy piece of coal, that's all. Calm down now! {from the book, lit: I'm sure a coal containing gas got mixed in}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.95,0:16:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Scary! {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.57,0:16:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay! Those firecrackers are something else! {bakuchi ga saiko}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.34,0:16:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Nicely done, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.94,0:16:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say "firecrackers"?! G-Girls!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.31,0:16:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be no history lesson this morning. \NI refuse to teach an unruly class like this! {from the book}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.22,0:17:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.63,0:17:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.63,0:17:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{???}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.00,0:17:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.93,0:17:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.74,0:17:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think she'd cry like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.67,0:17:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just an innocent prank. {lit: It was a bit of humour}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.62,0:17:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it, Pat! \NSo you were in on this too? {lit: how cruel, pat, you're an accomplice too?}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.09,0:17:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.08,0:17:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You all have no idea \Nhow much Miss Kennedy cares about us! {lit: too ignorant}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.42,0:17:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's Miss Kennedy's diary...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.49,0:17:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.45,0:17:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, she writes about you as well. Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.42,0:17:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm sure Pat will be interested in mythology..."
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.69,0:17:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"I want to tell Janet about Athena.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.66,0:17:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she's a strong-willed goddess, just like Janet..." {literally "tomboy goddess", but that's not exactly how you'd describe a goddess, but idk what other word could go here since athena is well-defined in the world's history as "associated with wisdom, warfare, and handicraft" and the japanese "otenba" here is closer to "Strong and independent like a man" than to tomboy; TLDR: to call her tomboy would be factually incorrect, to call her masculine would be insulting to janet...}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.17,0:17:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something about me.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.74,0:17:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It has my name written there too! {meaning "there's something about me too"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.74,0:17:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy blamed herself \Nfor not managing to teach us properly.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.80,0:17:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you ever seen \Nanyone so big-hearted? {lit: are there people with such a beautiful heart}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.60,0:18:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The kindest, most genuine people \Noften find it hardest to show it.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.62,0:18:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m ashamed to even be in the same class as you, \Nwhen you can’t even see that!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.66,0:18:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.02,0:18:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened here?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.41,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Miss Roberts...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.11,0:18:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What was all that noise?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.13,0:18:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And where is Miss Kennedy?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.58,0:18:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.02,0:18:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you—what did you do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.10,0:18:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We only... {/actually/you see}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.62,0:18:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Yikes!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.18,0:18:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on with that stove?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.42,0:18:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone put firecrackers in it?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.03,0:18:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.30,0:18:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.04,0:18:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to the common room \Nacross the passage.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.36,0:19:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect the girl who played this stupid \Nand dangerous joke to come and own up at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.98,0:19:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.95,0:19:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did it have to come to this?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.05,0:19:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts won't let me off the hook for this! {lit: will not forget - could mean anything}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.12,0:19:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m in for it now... {from book; lit: I have no choice but to go}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.23,0:19:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, I'm coming too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.06,0:19:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.76,0:19:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I egged you on to put \Nthose firecrackers in the stove.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.97,0:19:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d be an awful coward \Nif I let you go on your own.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.84,0:19:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.90,0:19:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You got the squibs and put them in—\Nbut I shared that joke with you, {lit: if I'm with you, I enjoyed your prank with you}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.04,0:19:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with no consideration \Nfor Miss Kennedy's feelings.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.19,0:19:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.71,0:19:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.71,0:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you girls are going, then, sure enough, I must come along too, as the head-girl of the class.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.67,0:19:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.69,0:19:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.62,0:19:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.68,0:19:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go too!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.61,0:19:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{I'm going too}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.19,0:19:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess our whole class \Nis to blame for this prank.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.69,0:19:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all go, then!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.08,0:19:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.30,0:20:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.95,0:20:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.70,0:20:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to give Miss Kennedy a scare...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.87,0:20:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But we were all a part of it! {lit: we also insitgated her}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.98,0:20:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.32,0:20:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.82,0:20:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you found it within yourselves to own up to it. {lit: I'm happy you graciously/nobly admitted to it}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.94,0:20:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that your camaraderie is so strong. {lit: and your friendship too}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.41,0:20:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, you'll still face punishment \Nfor what you did today. {lit: I'll make sure you pay ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.38,0:20:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.33,0:20:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we’ll deduct the cost of repairing \Nthe stove from everyone’s pocket money. {in book: Well, you will all share the expenses of the chimney being swept }
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.39,0:20:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.24,0:20:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{???}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.84,0:20:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, you forfeit your free time today.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.54,0:20:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you’ll use that time to tidy up \Nthe mess you’ve made in the classroom. {lit: clean the dirty places in the classroom}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.51,0:20:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.73,0:20:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.12,0:20:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.67,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.86,0:20:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.64,0:21:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.39,0:21:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.50,0:21:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wanted to play a little prank on you. \NI never meant to hurt you! I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.10,0:21:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We allowed ourselves to think little of you, \Nsince you were Miss Lewis' substitute.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.61,0:21:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we're awfully ashamed of it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.44,0:21:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We've come to realize how kind-hearted \Nand considerate you are!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.46,0:21:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy, we're sorry! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.38,0:21:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.50,0:21:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.59,0:21:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.26,0:21:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy, I won't play \Npranks like that ever again.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.19,0:21:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.13,0:21:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy, I'll do my best \Nto come to love history!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.63,0:21:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.53,0:21:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.17,0:21:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was myself always timid and not at all \Nlike a teacher. I promise to be stronger now. {lit: from now on for sure}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.72,0:21:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a wonderful teacher, the best ever! \NWe want to see you act a lot more confident!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.44,0:21:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A hundred times more! {lit: 100 times the present}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.38,0:21:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand times more!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.58,0:21:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy, you can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.21,0:21:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To see you girls so united in this drive...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.55,0:21:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because someone showed us. {lit: thanks to someone}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.25,0:21:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.45,0:22:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Though they're stubborn at times,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.65,0:22:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they can be really caring too!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.59,0:22:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{Huh?}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.57,0:22:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then. We've got a classroom \Nto tidy up. Right, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.19,0:22:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.33,0:22:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going first!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:15.00,0:22:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, me!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:16.00,0:22:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, {\i1}I'm{\i0} going first!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.60,0:23:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.92,0:23:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.79,0:23:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel, Janet received some sweets from home for her birthday celebration.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.02,0:23:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean \Nwe'll be having a midnight party?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.26,0:23:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! For some reason, eating in the middle of the night is so thrilling and delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.96,0:23:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. {??? sounds like disagreement, something like "but it's late"}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.10,0:23:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's bring Sheila and the others onboard \Nand do it in the class!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.20,0:23:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed! The more the merrier! {lit: it's going to be lively}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.92,0:23:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh! Not so loud, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.67,0:24:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.07,0:24:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Great Midnight Feast." {from the book}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.36,0:24:04.86,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 5\NThe Great Midnight Feast {真夜中のパーティー}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.37,0:24:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
